{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:34.247607+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 14cdb62b2e100f4ebf75f88cf5c58669437208e3)", "id": "lc_29564dff-cbf9-442e-aed0-de40c09e4856"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# vue3-vite-starter-template\n\nA single page app [Vite](https://vitejs.dev) starter template, created to easily bootstrap Vue.js 3 apps.\n\n**Features**\n\n- Vitest for unit testing\n- Pinia for state management\n- Vue Router 4 for client-side routing\n- Bootstrap 5.3 for layout and styling\n- SCSS variables inside Vue components\n- Purgecss for eliminating unused CSS\n- Basic multiple layouts feature\n- ESLint config based on `eslint:recommended` with sensible defaults :relaxed:\n- [Prettier](https://prettier.io/) for code formatting\n- Automated release workflow with [semantic-release](https://github.com/semantic-release/semantic-release)\n\n## Project setup\n\n```\npnpm install\n```\n\n### Compiles and hot-reloads for development\n\n```\npnpm run dev\n```\n\n### Compiles and minifies for production\n\n```\npnpm run build\n```\n\n## Run your unit tests\n\n```\npnpm run test:unit\n```\n\n### Lints files\n\n```\npnpm run lint\n```\n\n### Lints and fixes files\n\n```\nnpm run lint-fix\n```\n\n### Customize configuration\n\nSee [Configuration Reference](https://vitejs.dev/guide/).\n", "id": "lc_2551d92e-5743-4cb0-931e-ed2b9e9973c0"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "736a8113-3509-4929-94f0-3cfbb7604ed3", "tool_call_id": "call_f34b1db722c94fdcbd72fc49", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:34.247978+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 14e35346190d0ff04ea56d634a34dbac593ed1c9)", "id": "lc_951bac71-9e3e-4c10-b473-98467df860d5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"name\": \"vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"description\": \"Vue.js 3 Vite starter template with Pinia, Vue Router, Bootstrap and more.\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0-semantic-release\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"repository\": \"https://github.com/kouts/vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\",\n    \"build-preview\": \"vite build && vite preview\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"lint-fix\": \"eslint --fix \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"test:unit\": \"vitest\",\n    \"test:unit-coverage\": \"vitest run --coverage\",\n    \"prepare\": \"husky\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"bootstrap\": \"^5.3.8\",\n    \"jsdom\": \"^27.1.0\",\n    \"pinia\": \"^3.0.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^4.0.6\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.6.3\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@commitlint/cli\": \"^20.1.0\",\n    \"@commitlint/config-conventional\": \"^20.0.0\",\n    \"@fullhuman/postcss-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@fullhuman/vue-cli-plugin-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@kouts/eslint-config\": \"^3.0.9\",\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^6.0.1\",\n    \"@vue/compiler-sfc\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"@vue/test-utils\": \"^2.4.6\",\n    \"autoprefixer\": \"^10.4.21\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^9.39.0\",\n    \"husky\": \"^9.1.7\",\n    \"lint-staged\": \"^16.2.6\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.6.2\",\n    \"sass\": \"^1.93.3\",\n    \"vite\": \"^7.1.12\",\n    \"vite-plugin-html\": \"^3.2.2\"\n  }\n}", "id": "lc_937fc367-fc1e-4541-80c6-412bf92c2fa9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "15f82c1d-284e-429e-b694-0d7f217d591b", "tool_call_id": "call_435a14ccf27743ec9da7aa92", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:48.735823+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository evidence, **contributors are expected to use pnpm, and npm is explicitly not acceptable**.\n\n## Evidence from the repository\n\n### 1. **`package.json` — Hard enforcement**\n\n```json\n\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\",\n\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n```\n\nThe `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` script is a **hard gate**: it runs before `npm install` or `yarn install` would execute and will **abort the installation** if any package manager other than pnpm is used. This is the most direct evidence that npm is explicitly blocked.\n\nAdditionally, `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` (a [Corepack](https://nodejs.org/api/corepack.html) field) further signals pnpm is the canonical package manager, and Corepack can auto-enforce this.\n\n### 2. **`README.md` — pnpm commands throughout**\n\nThe project setup and all scripts in the README use `pnpm`:\n\n```\npnpm install\npnpm run dev\npnpm run build\npnpm run test:unit\npnpm run lint\n```\n\nThere is one instance of `npm run lint-fix` in the README, but this appears to be a typo/inconsistency since every other command uses `pnpm`.\n\n### 3. **Lock file: `pnpm-lock.yaml`**\n\nThe repository ships with a `pnpm-lock.yaml` file (not `package-lock.json`), which means the deterministic dependency resolution is tied to pnpm. Using `npm install` would generate a different lock file and potentially resolve different dependency versions.\n\n## Conclusion\n\n**Only pnpm is acceptable.** The repository enforces this at install time via `npx only-allow pnpm`, declares the expected version via the `packageManager` field, and provides a pnpm-specific lock file. Using npm would be blocked by the preinstall script and would also risk inconsistent dependency resolution.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 608, "prompt_tokens": 5482, "total_tokens": 6090, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 181, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4416, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0010085676, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0004796076, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00052896}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962334-J3ynp8HZlkWNV5ngzh9J", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a0-9629-7171-820b-e638ebc00b98-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5482, "output_tokens": 608, "total_tokens": 6090, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4416}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 181}}}}]}}}
